    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>STEERING COLUMN</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the right and left mounting brackets (
                    <hotlnk document="s05008t_2.xml" xrefid="f0500801">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the end covers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the horn contact spring and horn ring assembly by sliding them off the upper
                    shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0500805">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0500805" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500805" filename="../figg05/G0500805.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Steering Column Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TOP END COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HORN SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HOUSING AND PLATE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. LOWER COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. TURN SIGNAL-HAZARD SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. STEERING COLUMN</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. WIRING HARNESS</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. BOTTOM END COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. UPPER COVER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the upper column cover, making sure the tilt lever and turn signal switch lever
                    clear the slots. Remove the lower cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0500805">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the horn brush assembly. It is pressed into place and should be removed by gently
                    tapping it out toward the steering wheel end of the column.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turn signal-hazard switch assembly and wiring harness (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0500805">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>The tilt-only steering column is replaced as a unit. Do not attempt to disassemble or modify
                        this unit. The steering column unit is under spring tension and serious injury may result if
                        disassembly is attempted.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
